Create New Session - Success: for refresh session

request.description:
Create Session

Request

applicationId- is a string in UUID format. The application gets it from CI.
deviceType - is a string
The application can understood what is the platform it is working with help of dart.io package:

Response

accessToken - is a string in UUID format.
This token the application must send in every other request.
refreshToken - is a string in UUID format. This token the application will use in case of it received 403 code from any request from the backend. important!!! The fileStorage - is not the backend.

Errors

There is no validation for deviceType, it is possible to send any value.
In case of not valid applicationId string - the API returns 4xx exception.

request.description:
Partial Authorization

Request

username - a string, without any validation
password - a string, without any validation
type - a string, type of login/registration, possible values: email, apple, facebook, google
step - a string, the current "page/screen" where a user stays.
collectedData - a map (string, object), here client puts data that it collected during the "feature step", for example in case of social login - BE expects to get credentials data from 3td parties (full object of "get facebook token", "get apple credentials")

Response

originalUserId - a string, if returned not null, it means that the user logged in, but the application should still follow the instructions from "flowConfiguration"
flowConfiguration - a json array that presents instructions for the next steps in the onboarding flow.
